e real risk is that PR lookup itself might fail to find merged PRs, which pushes this to Integration minimum. Behavior 6 involves git operations around rebases and squash merges where commit hashes change but the branch shouldn't be flagged as stale work anymore—the failure mode hinges on how the staleness detection handles these git state changes.\n\nI can't mock this with a fake since rebases and squash merges need actual git operations to produce the real commit hash changes. I need a real local git repo to test whether the detection correctly stops flagging a branch after it's been squash merged into main with different commit hashes. That's Integration with real local git.\n\nMinimum: Integration\n\nNow let me wrap up the full list. PR state lookup wired with classification. Yes, could potentially be Unit if pure function gets PR data as input... let me reconsider.\n\nFor behavior 5, if the classifier function takes PR state as a parameter, then testing \"if PR exists, don't classify as stale\" is Unit. But the behavior says \"branches with open or merged PRs are not flagged\" which implies the full detection pipeline including PR lookup. I'll keep Integration but note it could be argued as Unit if the classifier is pure.\n\nFor behavior 6, integration with real local git is needed because we need to actually perform squash merges and test the detection logic against real commit hash changes.\n\nNow I'm assigning probability distributions across test levels for each behavior, starting with the integration tests and working through the rest.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9843,"cache_read_input_tokens":3199,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":9843},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"330405d7-b6aa-4d06-9284-c805b124e4a6","uuid":"ad1dd8